    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To calculate the Ankle Brachial Index (ABI) for peripheral arterial disease (PAD).",
        "keywords": [
          "ABI",
          "ankle",
          "brachial",
          "index",
          "PAD",
          "peripheral",
          "arterial",
          "disease",
          "risk",
          "foot",
          "blood",
          "pressure"
        ],
        "use": "Use to calculate the Ankle Brachial Index (ABI) for peripheral arterial disease (PAD).\n\nThe two formulas used are:\nRight ABI = Highest pressure in right foot / Highest pressure in both arms\nLeft ABI = Highest pressure in left foot / Highest pressure in both arms\n\nInterpretation \nABI value \t Vessel structure interpretation\tRecommendation\n1.0 - 1.4            Normal\t                                        None\n0.9 - 1.0\t         Acceptable\t                                None\n0.8 - 0.9\t         Some Arterial Disease\t                Treat risk factors\n0.5 - 0.8\t         Moderate Arterial Disease\t        Refer to vascular specialist\n<0.5\t         Severe Arterial Disease\t                Refer to vascular specialist",
        "copyright": "Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "Aboyans V, Criqui MH, Abraham P, Allison MA, Creager MA, Diehm C, Fowkes FG, Hiatt WR, JÃ¶nsson B, Lacroix P, Marin B, McDermott MM, Norgren L, Pande RL, Preux PM, Stoffers HE, Treat-Jacobson D; American Heart Association Council on Peripheral Vascular Disease; Council on Epidemiology and Prevention; Council on Clinical Cardiology; Council on Cardiovascular Nursing; Council on Cardiovascular Radiology and Intervention, and Council on Cardiovascular Surgery and Anesthesia. Measurement and interpretation of the ankle-brachial index: a scientific statement from the American Heart Association. Circulation. 2012 Dec 11;126(24):2890-909. doi: 10.1161/CIR.0b013e318276fbcb. Epub 2012 Nov 16. Erratum in: Circulation. 2013 Jan 1;127(1):e264. PMID: 23159553."
    }
  },
